GET_ALARM_ISREPEAT_AM - Static variable in interface com.ihealth.communication.control.AmProfile
The key of whether alarm repeat or not.
If value is true, it indicates that alarm will repeat as following values: AmProfile.GET_ALARM_WEEK_SUNDAY_AM AmProfile.GET_ALARM_WEEK_MONDAY_AM AmProfile.GET_ALARM_WEEK_TUESDAY_AM AmProfile.GET_ALARM_WEEK_WEDNESDAY_AM AmProfile.GET_ALARM_WEEK_THURSDAY_AM AmProfile.GET_ALARM_WEEK_FRIDAY_AM AmProfile.GET_ALARM_WEEK_SATURDAY_AM If the value is false, it indicates that alarm will only play one time.

getOfflineData() - Method in class com.ihealth.communication.control.ABPMControl
Get the value of historical data in the ABPM This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately. If get successfully, following callback will be triggered:
iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
The action is BpProfile.ACTION_HISTORICAL_DATA_BP. The keys of the message will show in KeyList of the action. If error happens, following callback will be triggered:
iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
The action will be BpProfile.ACTION_ERROR_BP The message will be a JSON string with error ID and description,
the keys will show in the KeyList of the action.

getOfflineData(int, int) - Method in class com.ihealth.communication.control.Hs5Control
Get offline data of specified user This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately. If get successfully, following callback will be triggered:
iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
The action is HsProfile.ACTION_NO_HISTORICALDATA or HsProfile.ACTION_HISTORICAL_DATA_HS. The keys of message will show in the KeyList of the action. If error happens, following callback will be triggered:
iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
The action will be HsProfile.ACTION_ERROR_HS The message will be a JSON string with error ID and description,
the keys will show in the KeyList of the action.
